    • Method Detail

      • getNthInSequence

        private IGrammarSymbol getNthInSequence(IGrammarSymbol h,
                                        int n)
        Convenience method that returns the n'th symbol in a sequence. Note that that unless the symbol is the last symbol in the sequence, the SequenceSymbol itself will be returned.
        Parameters:
        h - The start of the sequence. Unless n=0, this should be a SequenceSymbol
        n - The element in the sequence to return. 0 = the first symbol
        Returns:
        A SequenceSymbol, unless n refers to the last symbol in a sequence, where it will be the symbol itself.
